<HEADLINE> Marijuana Plants Discovered in Raid  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS OSOS, Calif. (AP) -- More than 5,000 marijuana plants were
found Tuesday at a private ranch in a rugged mountainous area, and
two people were arrested during a morning raid.
</P>
<P>
   The seized plants may have had a street value as high as $15
million, said Sgt. Sean Donahue of the San Luis Obispo County
Sheriff's Department.
</P>
<P>
   Grown with use of a sophisticated watering system, the marijuana
plants up to eight feet high were found in an area of steep terrain
surrounded by thick shrubs, Donahue said. The property's owner was
not a suspect, sheriff's narcotics detectives said.
</P>
<P>
   Two men were arrested on charges of conspiracy to distribute
marijuana. Bail for each man was set at $50,000.
</P>
