<HEADLINE> Fairly Strong Quake Hits N. Japan  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- A fairly strong earthquake with a preliminary
magnitude of 5.9 jolted northern Japan Wednesday morning, while
moderate tremors continued to shake small islands off Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
   There were no immediate reports of damage or injuries from
either quake, local officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The quake in northern Japan was centered about 6 miles under the
ocean floor off the Nemuro peninsula, the Meteorological Agency
said. It struck at 5:21 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   Nemuro, an eastern port city on Japan's northern main island of
Hokkaido, is about 600 miles northeast of Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, more moderate earthquakes jolted a string of volcanic
islands south of Tokyo, part of a series of tremors that has been
hitting the area since late June. No injuries or damages were
reported.
</P>
</TEXT>
