<HEADLINE> Ottawa 5, Buffalo 1 -- game 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   OTTAWA (AP) - Brad Rigby pitched five strong innings as the
Ottawa Lynx completed a doubleheader sweep of the Buffalo Bisons on
Tuesday night with a 5-1 victory in the nightcap.
</P>
<P>
   In the first game, Talmadge Nunnari drove in three runs to lead
Ottawa (47-70) to a 5-4 win.
</P>
<P>
   Rigby (3-6) stopped a personal six-game losing streak.
</P>
<P>
   Jaime Navarro (1-2) gave up five runs on 10 hits in five innings
for the Bisons (74-48).
</P>
<P>
   Brent Billingsley (8-8) pitched 5 2-3 innings to earn the win
for Ottawa in the first game. He allowed four runs, walked three
and struck out three.
</P>
<P>
   The game was shortened to 6&AMP;frac12; innings to accommodate both games.
</P>
<P>
   Guillermo Mota got the last out of the fifth and pitched a
perfect sixth for his seventh save of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Tim Drew (5-6) pitched a complete game for Buffalo in taking the
loss. He allowed 10 hits, struck out five and walked three.
</P>
