<HEADLINE> Wayne County man gets 25 years  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   LYONS, N.Y. (AP) - A Wayne County Court judge has sentenced a
man to spend 25 years in state prison for the kidnapping and rape
of a 7-year-old girl.
</P>
<P>
   Richard K. Allen Jr., 19, pleaded guilty Tuesday to
second-degree kidnapping, first-degree rape and first-degree
sodomy. Judge Stephen Sirkin levied the maximum sentences of 25
years for the kidnapping, rape and sodomy charges.
</P>
<P>
   ''He didn't want to go to trial, and he obviously didn't want to
cause the (victim's) family any more pain than it has been
caused,'' said Allen's lawyer, Wayne County Public Defender Ronald
Valentine.
</P>
<P>
   Allen's trial was scheduled to start Aug. 28.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm very pleased that we were able to obtain a conviction on
all counts with a maximum sentence without a trial, and the family
is likewise relieved that this is over with,'' said Wayne County
District Attorney Richard Healy.
</P>
<P>
   Allen also waived his right to appeal the conviction.
</P>
</TEXT>
