<HEADLINE> Marlins 7, Dodgers 3  </HEADLINE>
By STEVEN WINE
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Ryan Dempster allowed three hits in eight innings
and Luis Castillo had three hits to help the Florida Marlins beat
the Los Angeles Dodgers 7-3 Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Pinch-hitter F.P. Santangelo broke up Dempster's shutout bid
with his first homer of the year on the first pitch of the eighth.
It was the first run given up by Dempster in 14 career innings
against the Dodgers.
</P>
<P>
   Dempster (11-8) struck out eight, walked two and retired 15 of
16 batters during one stretch.
</P>
<P>
   Braden Looper gave up a two-run double to Chad Kreuter in the
ninth before Antonio Alfonseca retired the final three batters.
</P>
<P>
   The Marlins, who jumped on Kevin Brown for nine runs in the
first two innings of Monday's 11-2 victory, raced to a 5-0 lead
after three innings against rookie Matt Herges (8-2).
</P>
<P>
   Castillo finished 3-for-4 with a walk, raising his average to
.355. Henry Rodriguez and Preston Wilson each had two hits and two
RBIs.
</P>
<P>
   Dodgers slugger Gary Sheffield was ejected in the eighth inning
by rookie umpire Dan Iassogna. Sheffield was called out on strikes,
then ejected then he drew a line in the dirt with his bat,
indicating he thought the pitch was wide.
</P>
<P>
   Florida took advantage of sloppy fielding by second baseman Mark
Grudzielanek to score four runs in the third.
</P>
<P>
   Dempster led off with an infield single and Castillo walked.
Mark Kotsay hit a routine grounder to Grudzielanek, whose soft toss
to first sailed wild for an error, scoring one run. Rodriguez hit
another grounder off Grudzielanek's glove for a two-run single, and
after Wilson singled, Derrek Lee singled home another run.
</P>
<P>
   Wilson's sacrifice fly gave Florida a 1-0 lead in the first. He
doubled home a run in the seventh, then scored on a fielder's
choice.
</P>
<P>
   Herges, making his second major league start, pitched six
innings and allowed five runs, four earned.
</P>
<P>
   Dempster pitched around two errors by shortstop Andy Fox in the
first. Fox speared a sharp grounder by Eric Karros with a lunging
stop to end the inning and save a run.
</P>
<P>
Notes: The start was delayed by rain for the second consecutive
night, this time by 43 minutes. ... Dempster shut out the Dodgers
over seven innings in his only other appearance against them on
Sept. 7, 1999. ... Castillo's infield hit in the first inning was
his 44th, most in the major leagues. The three-hit game was his
10th this year. ... Neat feat: The Dodgers are just two games above
.500 but have a winning record both at home and on the road. ...
Herges lost on the road for the first time in seven decisions.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
