<HEADLINE> Athletics 5, Indians 3  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Ben Grieve homered and drove in two runs
as the Oakland Athletics defeated the Cleveland Indians 5-3 Tuesday
night.
</P>
<P>
   Matt Stairs also drove in two runs as the A's won for the third
time in four games following a season high six-game losing streak.
</P>
<P>
   Mark Mulder (7-8) won for just the second time since June 25, a
span of nine starts. He went six innings, allowing two runs on five
hits and three walks.
</P>
<P>
   Jason Isringhausen, who had two blown saves and a loss in his
previous three outings, recorded his 26th save in 33 opportunities
by pitching a scoreless ninth.
</P>
<P>
   Dave Burba (10-5) lost for the first time in six starts after
allowing four runs -- two earned -- on four hits and four walks. He
struck out eight in five innings.
</P>
<P>
   The A's beat the Indians for the second straight night and moved
two games ahead of them in the wild-card race. Cleveland lost for
just the fourth time in 13 games.
</P>
<P>
   Mulder survived a shaky first inning in which he walked the
bases loaded with one out, but then induced David Segui to ground
into an inning-ending double play.
</P>
<P>
   Burba walked the bases loaded in the first with two outs, and
the A's capitalized when Stairs doubled home two runs. Burba issued
four walks in the opening inning.
</P>
<P>
   The Indians responded with a run in the second. Wil Cordero
singled and eventually scored on Jolbert Cabrera's sacrifice fly.
</P>
<P>
   The A's added a pair of unearned runs in the second. With one
out, Randy Velarde was safe on second baseman Roberto Alomar's
fielding error. Miguel Tejada followed with a run-scoring double
and after Jason Giambi struck out, Grieve doubled home Tejada.
</P>
<P>
   Grieve hit his 22nd home run of the season, a solo shot off
Justin Speier with one out in the seventh.
</P>
<P>
   Segui scored Cleveland's second run on Einar Diaz's groundout in
the fourth. Manny Ramirez singled home Kenny Lofton in the eighth.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Segui, who has hit safely in 14 of the 15 games he's played
for the Indians, has not made an error in 45 games at first base.
... A's OF Terrence Long didn't start the game because of a rib
contusion on his right side, but did enter the game as a defensive
replacement. ... Burba has a 3.41 ERA since his last loss on July
6. ... All seven walks recorded by the starting pitchers came in
the first inning. ... Oakland has now scored first in three of its
last four games after not doing so in its previous 10 contests. ...
Lofton snapped an 0-for-14 streak with a single in the eighth.
</P>
