<TEXT>
<P>
	   HARTWICK, N.Y. (AP) - An Otsego County man doused his house,
restaurant and an apartment building with gasoline before setting
them ablaze, according to police.
</P>
<P>
   Eric H. Bryant, 35, faces four counts of third degree arson, a
felony, police said. Bryant remained in the Otsego County
Correctional Facility in lieu of $35,000 cash bail Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   The restaurant, as well as a single story apartment next door,
and Bryant's home next door to the apartment, in addition to a 1965
or 1966 Mustang parked behind the restaurant, were all fully in
flames when firefighters arrived, according to Hartwick Seminary
Fire Chief Tom Roseboom.
