<HEADLINE> Dow Slips 1; Nasdaq Climbs 23  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down one
point in today's early going. Advancing issues on the New York
Stock Exchange hold a 4-3 lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 23 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is up two points.
</P>
<P>
   Inflation data out today provide no cause for alarm for the
markets.
</P>
<P>
   The government says its consumer price index rose 0.2 percent in
July, generally in line with expectations.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts say the report gives no reason to challenge the
conventional wisdom that the Federal Reserve will leave rates alone
at its next policy meeting next week.
