<HEADLINE> Elderly Palestinian Man Killed  </HEADLINE>
By JASMINA KELEMEN
<TEXT>
<P>
   SURDA, West Bank (AP) -- An elderly Palestinian-American who
thought robbers were breaking into his house Wednesday fired his
pistol, prompting Israeli soldiers patrolling the area to fire
back, killing him.
</P>
<P>
   The incident, which some Israeli media described as a botched
military operation, drew a stiff rebuke from the Palestinian
Authority.
</P>
<P>
   ''The Palestinian Authority considers the killing of the
Palestinian citizen Mahmoud Abdullah as a crime,'' cabinet
secretary general Ahmed Abdel Rachman said in a press release. The
Authority called on the Israeli government to prosecute those
responsible.
</P>
<P>
   Mahmoud Abdullah, 70, opened fire from the roof of his house
before dawn as Israeli soldiers passed by. He apparently thought
the intruders were burglars. His house had been robbed several
weeks earlier.
</P>
<P>
   Israeli soldiers fired back, hitting Abdullah in the head and
mortally wounding him. The Israelis took his sons for questioning
and released them a few hours later.
</P>
<P>
   Reporting on the incident, an Israeli television news reporter
called it a series of mistakes by the military.
</P>
<P>
   Abdullah's son Hisham, a journalist with the Agence
France-Presse news agency, said Israeli army officers kept medics
away from the house for more than an hour.
</P>
<P>
   ''It was really a nightmare,'' Hisham Abdullah said. ''They
(Israeli troops) prevented anyone from reaching the house. For them
it was war. I tried to talk to them but they wouldn't stop
shooting.''
</P>
<P>
   Mahmoud Abdullah, who had lived in the U.S. Virgin Islands for
20 years, died in an ambulance on the way to a hospital, relatives
said. U.S. officials said he was a U.S. citizen.
</P>
<P>
   Col. Gal Hirsch, the Israeli army commander in the area, said
his forces had to make sure no gunmen were hiding in the area
before allowing medics into the Abdullah home. The Israelis said
the Abdullah home was not the object of their sweep through the
village, but they would not say what their mission was.
</P>
<P>
   The incident occurred around 3 a.m. in this village north of the
West Bank city of Ramallah. The village is in a part of the West
Bank where Palestinians and Israelis share control.
</P>
<P>
   Afterward, the front of the house was riddled with bullets,
including nine that struck the front door. On the roof, reporters
saw a large pool of blood. Soldiers searched the house and found
the pistol Abdullah had used.
</P>
<P>
   In tears after he and his brothers were questioned, Hisham
Abdullah said he was asked about matters that had nothing to do
with the shooting, such as whether he had acquaintances in Lebanon.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-08-16-00 1724 </TRAILER>
