<HEADLINE> Gloucester Township teacher charged with fondling students  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   CAMDEN, N.J. (AP) - A Gloucester Township teacher was indicted
Wednesday on charges that he fondled female students, the Camden
County Prosecutor's Office said.
</P>
<P>
   Peter Higginson, 44, of Clayton, a teacher at the Ann Mullen
School in Gloucester Township, was indicted by a grand jury on 23
counts, including sexual assault, aggravated criminal sexual
contact, endangering the welfare of a child and official
misconduct.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutor Lee Solomon said seven girls, ranging in age from 12
to 14, were victimized.
</P>
<P>
   Solomon said from the 1998-1999 school year through the
1999-2000 school year, Higginson inappropriately touched the
students, mostly on their buttocks.
</P>
<P>
   Higginson was arrested May 11 in connection with an alleged
incident that involved a 13-year-old student a week earlier on
school property, Solomon said in a prepared statement.
</P>
<P>
   Higginson is free on $50,000 bail.
</P>
<P>
   Greg Reinert, spokesman for the Prosecutor's Office, said the
incidents occurred in the school during school hours.
</P>
</TEXT>
