<HEADLINE> Madonna, Rocco Doing Fine  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Madonna and her son are fine, a spokeswoman
said Wednesday, disputing tabloid reports that the newborn has a
serious respiratory problem possibly caused by premature birth.
</P>
<P>
   The pop singer and her baby, Rocco Ritchie, ''are home and
they're well,'' spokeswoman Liz Rosenberg said from New York.
</P>
<P>
   She declined to discuss specifics of the child's health.
</P>
<P>
   The boy was born at an undisclosed hospital on Aug. 11.
</P>
<P>
   ''They were never in any life-threatening situation,'' Rosenberg
said. ''The baby was released a couple of days ago (from the
hospital) and everyone is well and thriving.''
</P>
<P>
   The Mirror of London, citing unidentified hospital sources,
reported Tuesday that the child had respiratory distress syndrome
and was being treated in the neonatal intensive care unit at
Cedars-Sinai Medical Center for complications with his lungs,
kidney and liver.
</P>
<P>
   The complications were consistent with the boy's birth three
weeks early, the tabloid said.
</P>
<P>
   The boy's father is British film director Guy Ritchie.
</P>
