<HEADLINE> Public Service Commission gives OK for NiMo rate reduction  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   SYRACUSE, N.Y. (AP) - Niagara Mohawk Power Corp. got the OK on
Wednesday from state officials to reduce delivery prices of
electricity for most of its customers, the utility announced.
</P>
<P>
   The reductions, which will begin in September, will amount to
nearly $19 million.
</P>
<P>
   Niagara Mohawk chairman William E. Davis said the new pricing
plan was ''an important step toward properly aligning prices with
actual costs so customers can make informed decisions in the
competitive marketplace.''
</P>
<P>
   According to the pricing plan approved by the New York State
Public Service Commission, residential and small commercial
customers will see average electricity delivery price reductions of
about 1.5 percent, while the utility's largest industrial customers
will receive reductions of about 1.9 percent.
</P>
