<HEADLINE> Man holds children against will  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   GLENS FALLS, N.Y. (AP) - A 58-year-old man has been charged with
enticing four children into his house with baked treats then
refusing to let them leave, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Kenneth Henkel is accused of inviting the children - ages 4 to
10 - into his home with a promise of cookies and pie Monday night.
Police said he fed the kids the goodies then became angry with them
and refused to let them leave for about five minutes.
</P>
<P>
   A neighbor who heard the crying knocked on the apartment door
and was pushed away and cursed by Henkel, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Henkel eventually let the children go unharmed but refused to
let police into his apartment for several minutes. After
surrendering, he refused to be photographed or fingerprinted and
has not spoken to police.
</P>
<P>
   Jailed without bail, he faces charges of unlawful imprisonment
and endangering the welfare of a child.
</P>
