<HEADLINE> Mexican Boy Found; American Missing  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY (AP) -- Rescuers found a 15-year-old Mexican boy
missing for over a week on a mountain-climbing trip, but the boy
told them the American man who was with him had fallen into a
ravine, Mexico's government news agency Notimex reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Jorge Romero was found Tuesday suffering from hypothermia and
dehydration, Notimex said. The boy told authorities that Rony Jasse
of Chicago fell into a deep ravine during a light rain shortly
after the two began their climb Aug. 6.
</P>
<P>
   U.S. volunteers and Mexican police were searching for Jasse, who
set out with Romero, his wife's cousin, to climb 14,330-foot Nevada
de Colima mountain near Mexico's southern Pacific Coast.
</P>
